# Post-Coding Checks (Cloud Orchestrator Review Gate)

Read when: a worker has returned a result packet with status DONE.
Skip when: status is BLOCKED; use `docs/INVESTIGATOR_PROTOCOL.md` after repeated BLOCKED.

Purpose: mandatory cloud review of every DONE packet. This substitutes for the operator reading code.

## Review Inputs
1. Original `docs/WORKER_TASK_PACKET.md`
2. Returned `docs/WORKER_RESULT_PACKET.md`
3. `git diff --stat` from the result packet
4. Full diff only when test honesty, scope, security, or evidence requires it
5. Touched rows of `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md`

## 1) Scope Verification
- [ ] Every changed file appears in Allowed Files
- [ ] No source file > 500 lines unless packet authorized refactor
- [ ] Iteration count <= Packet Class max
- [ ] Packet Class matches observed change shape
- [ ] Branch / rollback fields are filled for non-trivial work

## 2) Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Every PASS has an evidence pointer
- [ ] Every FAIL uses PARTIAL or BLOCKED, not DONE
- [ ] Spot-check at least one evidence pointer against actual command/log/test output
- [ ] Criteria prove real user behavior or data outcome, not only implementation existence

## 3) Test Honesty Spot-Check
If any test file changed:
- [ ] Pull full diff for test changes
- [ ] Assertions are at least as strict as before, or justification is credible
- [ ] No deleted/skipped tests without explicit authorization
- [ ] No `skip`, `xfail`, `it.skip`, or equivalent without justification
- [ ] New FEATURE / BUGFIX tests include RED evidence
- [ ] BUGFIX regression test would have failed against unfixed behavior
- [ ] New assertions are not tautologies such as checking only that a mocked call, variable, or function exists

## 4) Traceability Evidence
- [ ] Every Path ID listed in result has updated row or N/A rationale
- [ ] Required smoke command/runbook evidence exists
- [ ] No touched Path ID is left as `Coverage pending`
- [ ] Manual smoke evidence is concrete and current enough for the project tier
- [ ] State Mutation Index locations touched by this packet exist in the repo
- [ ] New workflows update `docs/WORKFLOW_TEST_MATRIX.md`
- [ ] New smokes update `docs/SMOKE_TEST_CATALOG.md`
- [ ] UI-visible changes include a manual click path, screenshot/trace, or browser-smoke evidence

## 5) Security / Privacy / Data Quick Pass
- [ ] No secret literals in source, docs, logs, or packet evidence
- [ ] No new public endpoint without auth note
- [ ] No new file-write path outside documented data directories
- [ ] No migration/data-loss risk without rollback note
- [ ] Persistent data/schema/storage changes have a pre-change snapshot/dump or explicit N/A rationale
- [ ] Data rollback steps are operator-executable, not just "revert the commit"
- [ ] Security scans promised in ops docs are actually run by local verify or CI, or the gap is recorded

## 6) Decision

| Outcome | Trigger | Action |
|---|---|---|
| ACCEPT | All sections pass | Approve reviewed outcome and record ledger result |
| REPAIR | One narrow gap | Issue small follow-up packet only for that gap |
| REJECT | Multiple gaps or test-honesty failure | Reissue corrected packet from PLAN step |
| ESCALATE | Root cause unclear or repeated failure | Use `docs/INVESTIGATOR_PROTOCOL.md` |

After decision, update `docs/state/packet_ledger.json` and `docs/state/session_budget.json` if this project uses state ledgers.
